# ğŸŒˆ Bonus Step 6: Put Your Website Online! ğŸŒ

This is the **coolest part** â€” letâ€™s put your website on the internet so anyone can visit it from their phone or computer!

Youâ€™ll do 3 things:
1. Create a **GitHub account** (if you donâ€™t have one)
2. Upload your code to a **GitHub repository**
3. Deploy it live using **Netlify** (for free!)

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 6.1: Create a GitHub Account

1. Go to [https://github.com](https://github.com)
2. Click **"Sign up"**
3. Choose a username (like `ali-codes`)
4. Enter your email and password
5. Complete the steps to create your account

âœ… Done! You now have a GitHub profile.

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 6.2: Create a New Repository

A **repository** (or "repo") is like a folder in the cloud for your code.

1. After logging in, click the **"+"** icon in the top right
2. Click **"New repository"**
3. Name it: `my-profile`
4. Choose **"Public"** (so others can see it)
5. Click **"Create repository"**

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 6.3: Upload Your Files

Now, upload your `profile.html` (and your photo) to GitHub:

1. In your repo, click **"Add file" â†’ "Upload files"**
2. Drag and drop:
   - `profile.html`
   - Your photo (e.g., `me.jpg`)
3. Click **"Commit changes"** at the bottom

âœ… Your code is now on GitHub!

Your website code is live on the internet â€” but not viewable as a webpage yet. Letâ€™s fix that!

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 6.4: Deploy to Netlify (Free & Easy!)

Weâ€™ll use **Netlify** to turn your code into a real website URL like:  
ğŸ‘‰ `https://ali-codes.netlify.app`

#### Step 1: Go to Netlify
Open this link: [https://app.netlify.com/drop](https://app.netlify.com/drop)

#### Step 2: Drag and Drop!
- Open your project folder on your computer
- Select both `profile.html` and your image
- Drag them into the Netlify page
- Wait a few secondsâ€¦

ğŸ‰ **Boom!** Netlify builds your site and gives you a live link!

Example: `https://clever-squirrel-123.netlify.app`

> ğŸ”— You can click the link and share it with anyone!

---

### ğŸ”¹ Step 6.5: (Optional) Connect Netlify to GitHub

Want your site to update automatically when you make changes? Letâ€™s connect GitHub!

1. Go to [https://app.netlify.com](https://app.netlify.com)
2. Sign in with GitHub
3. Click **"New site from Git"**
4. Choose **GitHub** â†’ select your `my-profile` repo
5. Click **"Deploy site"**

Now, every time you update your code on GitHub, Netlify will automatically update your live site! ğŸ”„

